<topic id='business_definition_group_therapy.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Group Therapy - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_group_therapy">Group Therapy</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_session">SESSION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_group_therapy">Group Therapy</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_session">SESSION</xref>
 where more than one 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 attends at the same time, to see one or more 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
(s).  Clinical notes are recorded in each individual 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 record.  </p>
  <p>
For the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_community_services_data_set">Community Services Data Set</xref>
, 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_group_therapy">Group Therapy</xref>
 is recorded as a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_contact">CARE CONTACT</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
Note: 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_group_session">Group Sessions</xref>
 are recorded when the attendees at the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_session">SESSION</xref>
 are not known in advance, and clinical notes are not made in individual 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 records.  </p>

